				<h1>Sweating The Small Stuff</h1>
				<p>
					Websites are no longer made up of static pages. Between the varying device sizes we have to tackle and design systems that are becoming ever more complex, they simply don’t hold up to the challenges we’re faced with on the web today. Brian Graves and Ryan Heap take a look at using a combination of Style Tiles and Atomic Design to create design systems that can take content all of the places it needs to go and keep it looking great, extendable and user friendly along the way.
				</p>
